commit.message:
README.md: remove duplicate m4 dependency line

M4 is mentioned as a dependency twice. Remove one of
the lines.

Signed-off-by: Hans Holmberg <hans.holmberg@wdc.com>

Version 2.0.4

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@opensource.wdc.com>

tools: gzbd: Fix signale handler function

printf() is not a reentrant function and so not safe to use in a signal
handler. Remove this function call from dz_sig_handler().

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@opensource.wdc.com>

tools: gui: add pthread library

Add -lpthread to libraries used for final linking.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@opensource.wdc.com>

libzbd.spec: remove dependendy on autoconf-archive

Not needed.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@opensource.wdc.com>

tools: viewer: remove unneeded header file

pthread.h is not needed.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@opensource.wdc.com>

configure: remove dependency on autoconf-archive

Remove the dependency on autoconf-archive by avoiding using macros such
as AX_CHECK_ENABLE_DEBUG and AX_PTHREAD. Also change AC_CONFIG_HEADER to
AC_CONFIG_HEADERS.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@opensource.wdc.com>

Version 2.0.3

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@opensource.wdc.com>

Makefile: remove source tar file after rpm build

Make sure to delete the source tar file used to build rpms once the rpms
are built.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@opensource.wdc.com>

Fix warning unitialized variable `ret` in `zbd_report_zones`

Initialize variable `ret` to avoid the following warning:

```
/libzbd/lib/zbd.c:625:9: error:
variable 'ret' may be uninitialized when used here
[-Werror,-Wconditional-uninitialized]
        return ret;
```

Signed-off-by: Luis Donoso <luis.donoso@percona.com>

Sync debian packaging files

Signed-off-by: Sudip Mukherjee <sudipm.mukherjee@gmail.com>

Version 2.0.2

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

Makefile: distclean configure, rpm and source tar files

Remove the configure script, rpm files and .tar.gz source file when
running "make distclean". For "make clean", keep the configure script.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

README.md: clarify requirements

Clarify that GTK3 and its development headers are required to build the
gzbd and gzbd-viewer applications by mentioning these in the requirement
list.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

configure: fix typo

gzviewer mention in GTK3 check should be gzbd-viewer.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

build: rpm: point to source tar.gz file as the source

In the rpm spec file, change Source0 to point to a "make dist" generated
tar.gz file to avoid problems with distro RPM build systems complaining
about MD5sum check errors due to differences between "make dist" file
and the github automatically generated source tar file.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

tools: gzbd-viewer: Add icon and desktop file

Add an icon and a .desktop file for the gzbd-viewer tool to integrate
it with the desktop environment.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

tools: gzbd-viewer: Increase minimum width

Increase the minimum width so that the legend is completely displayed.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

tools: gzbd-viewer: check user ID

Root priviledges are needed to open a block device file. Check that the
user ID is root before trying to open a device.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

tools: gzbd-viewer: use file chooser to select device

When no device file is specified on the command line, use the file
chooser dialog to select one.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

tools: gzbd: Add icon and desktop file

Add an icon and a .desktop file for the gzbd tool to integrate it with
the desktop environment.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

tools: gzbd: check user ID

Check that the effective uid off the user is root to ensure that
zoned block devices can be open.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

tools: gzbd: introduce dz_if_err() helper

Introduce the dz_if_err() helper to open a modal window displaying
error messages.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

tools: gzbd: use /dev as the initial folder

When starting the file chooser dialog to select a device to open, set
the initial folder to "/dev" and show only block device files.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

Version 2.0.1

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@opensource.wdc.com>

lib: fix zbd_get_info() export

Correctly export zbd_get_info() as a library public function by fixing
the incorrect function name in lib/exports (zbd_get_device_info ->
zbd_get_info).

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@opensource.wdc.com>

Version 2.0.0

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

rpm: update spec file

Cleanup libzbd rpm spec file.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

configure: Add call to AC_CANONICAL_TARGET

This fixes the warning:

configure.ac:30: warning: AC_ARG_PROGRAM was called before AC_CANONICAL_TARGET

with autoconf 2.69.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>

libzbd: Improve RPM package build

Simplify the "make rpm" directive and modify libzbd spec file to create
separate RPM packages for the command line and GTK tools.

Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@opensource.wdc.com>
